@{
    ViewBag.Title = "ToolBar and ButtonEx";
}

<partial name="~/Demos/Shared/_Index.cshtml" />
<h2>@ViewBag.Title</h2>

<div>
    <p>The <code>tp.ButtonEx</code> control is button class with ico and text. It actually is an anchor element. Used by the <code>tp.ToolBar</code> control. </p>
    <p>The <code>tp.ToolBar</code> control is a tool-bar.</p>
    <p>Both classes provide properties to handle the display of the buttons regarding the Text and the Icon.</p>
</div>

<br />



<div class="html-code">
    <div>
        <button onclick="ToggleNoText()">Toggle NoText</button> <br /> <br />
        <button onclick="ToggleIcoMode()">Toggle IcoMode</button> <br />
    </div>
    <br />

